physicalEntities.name: physicalEntities
physicalEntities.contactinfo: Contact: Customer Service Tel: 1-877-526-2278 ext 136 Fax: 1-603-594-2887 Web: info@lancast.com
physicalEntities.description: This is the enterprise MIB definition file for the Physical Entities of Lancast Managed products. Copyright 1999 Lancast Inc.

chassisTable.name: chassisTable
chassisTable.description: A table of relevent information pertaining to each chassis contained within this system.

chassisTableEntry.name: chassisTableEntry
chassisTableEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing relevant information about a specific chassis contained within this system.

chassisEntityIndex.name: chassisEntityIndex
chassisEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, which identifies this chassis.

chassisDescription.name: chassisDescription
chassisDescription.description: A textual string describing a chassis contained within this system.

chassisPartNumber.name: chassisPartNumber
chassisPartNumber.description: A textual string of the part number assigned to this chassis.

chassisNumSlots.name: chassisNumSlots
chassisNumSlots.description: The number of I/O slots that this chassis supports.

chassisCurrentTemp.name: chassisCurrentTemp
chassisCurrentTemp.description: The temperature of this chassis measured in Celcius degrees. This object will be contained in the tempStatusChange trap,

chassisMaxTemp.name: chassisMaxTemp
chassisMaxTemp.description: The maximum temperature for this chassis. If this temperature is exceeded failures may result. This object will be contained in the tempStatusChange Trap,

chassisReset.name: chassisReset
chassisReset.description: The trigger to reset this chassis. If the design of this chassis does not include this feature then this object will default to not-resetable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit a reset then the only valid state that a user can set this object to is is reset. A read of this object will return either resetable or not-resetable.

lastEntityResetReason.name: lastEntityResetReason
lastEntityResetReason.description: This object specifies the reason the last reset was applied. This object is included in the entityResetTrap pdu.

lastEntityResetIndex.name: lastEntityResetIndex
lastEntityResetIndex.description: This object specifies the physical entity index, entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, of the last entity that was reset. This object is included in the entityResetTrap pdu.

lastEntityResetTime.name: lastEntityResetTime
lastEntityResetTime.description: This object specifies the time the last reset was applied to an entity. This object is included in the entityResetTrap pdu.

lastEntityResetType.name: lastEntityResetType
lastEntityResetType.description: This object specifies the type of entity that was last reset. The values are are a subset from the entity mib entPhysicalClass object.

backPlaneTable.name: backPlaneTable
backPlaneTable.description: A table of relevent information pertaining to a backplane contained within this system.

backPlaneTableEntry.name: backPlaneTableEntry
backPlaneTableEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing relevant information about a specific backplane contained within this system.

backPlaneEntityIndex.name: backPlaneEntityIndex
backPlaneEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a back plane for which this entry contains information.

backPlaneDescription.name: backPlaneDescription
backPlaneDescription.description: A textual string describing a backPlane contained within this system.

backPlanePartNumber.name: backPlanePartNumber
backPlanePartNumber.description: A textual string of the part number of this back plane.

backPlaneSerialNumber.name: backPlaneSerialNumber
backPlaneSerialNumber.description: A textual string of the serial number of this back plane.

backPlaneManufactureDate.name: backPlaneManufactureDate
backPlaneManufactureDate.description: A textual string of the manufacture date of this back plane.

backPlaneHWRevisionNumber.name: backPlaneHWRevisionNumber
backPlaneHWRevisionNumber.description: A textual string of the hardware revision date of this back plane.

powerSupplyTable.name: powerSupplyTable
powerSupplyTable.description: A table of relevent information pertaining to a backplane contained within this system.

powerSupplyTableEntry.name: powerSupplyTableEntry
powerSupplyTableEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing relevant information about a specific backplane contained within this system.

powerSupplyEntityIndex.name: powerSupplyEntityIndex
powerSupplyEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a power supply for which this entry contains information.

powerSupplyStatus.name: powerSupplyStatus
powerSupplyStatus.description: The on off state of this power supply.

powerSupplyType.name: powerSupplyType
powerSupplyType.description: The type of this power supply.

powerSupply5vCurrent.name: powerSupply5vCurrent
powerSupply5vCurrent.description: The actual voltage level of this 5 volt supply as measured in millivolts.

powerSupply5vMin.name: powerSupply5vMin
powerSupply5vMin.description: The minimum operating voltage level of this 5 volt supply, measured in millivolts.

powerSupply5vMax.name: powerSupply5vMax
powerSupply5vMax.description: The maximum operating voltage level of this 5 volt supply, measured in millivolts.

moduleTable.name: moduleTable
moduleTable.description: A table of common information relevent to modules within this system.

moduleTableEntry.name: moduleTableEntry
moduleTableEntry.description: An entry in the common module information table.

modEntityIndex.name: modEntityIndex
modEntityIndex.description: A unique value, entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a module for which this entry contains information.

modAdminState.name: modAdminState
modAdminState.description: The desired state of up or down of this module. If the design of this module does not include the abiltiy to control this module then this object will default to not-applicable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit control then up and down are the valid states that a user can set this object to.

modOperStatus.name: modOperStatus
modOperStatus.description: The current operational (up/down) state of this module.

modType.name: modType
modType.description: The type of module resident in this system.

modDescription.name: modDescription
modDescription.description: A textual description of this type of module.

modName.name: modName
modName.description: A user defined name for this module.

modPartNumber.name: modPartNumber
modPartNumber.description: A textual string identifying the part number of this module.

modSerialNumber.name: modSerialNumber
modSerialNumber.description: A textual string identifying the serieal number of this module.

modManufactureDate.name: modManufactureDate
modManufactureDate.description: A textual string identifying the date that this module was manufactured.

modDiagnosticTestStatus.name: modDiagnosticTestStatus
modDiagnosticTestStatus.description: A textual string indicating the status of the last diagnostic test performed on this module including the date and time.

modHWRevisionNumber.name: modHWRevisionNumber
modHWRevisionNumber.description: A textual string identifying the hardware revision number of this module.

modNumPorts.name: modNumPorts
modNumPorts.description: The number of ports conntained within this module.

modFirstSlot.name: modFirstSlot
modFirstSlot.description: The first slot which is the leftmost slot that this module physically resides in.

modNumSlotsOccupied.name: modNumSlotsOccupied
modNumSlotsOccupied.description: The total number of slots that this module physically occupies.

modReset.name: modReset
modReset.description: The trigger to reset this module. If the design of this module does not include this feature then this object will default to not-resetable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit a reset then the only valid state that a user can set this object to is is reset. A read of this object will return either resetable or not-resetable.

mgmntTable.name: mgmntTable
mgmntTable.description: A table of information common to management modules within this system.

mgmntTableEntry.name: mgmntTableEntry
mgmntTableEntry.description: An entry in the managment module information table.

mgmntEntityIndex.name: mgmntEntityIndex
mgmntEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a managemnt module for which this entry contains information.

mgmntBootImageName.name: mgmntBootImageName
mgmntBootImageName.description: A textual description of the name of the Boot image.

mgmntBootImageVersion.name: mgmntBootImageVersion
mgmntBootImageVersion.description: A textual description of the version of the Boot image The vesion will include the time and date of the build.

mgmntCoreImageName.name: mgmntCoreImageName
mgmntCoreImageName.description: A textual description of the name of the Core image.

mgmntCoreImageVersion.name: mgmntCoreImageVersion
mgmntCoreImageVersion.description: A textual description of the version of the Core image The vesion will include the time and date of the build.

mgmntAppImageName.name: mgmntAppImageName
mgmntAppImageName.description: A textual description of the name of the Application (personality) image.

mgmntAppImageVersion.name: mgmntAppImageVersion
mgmntAppImageVersion.description: A textual description of the version of the Application (personality) image. The vesion will include the time and date of the build.

mgmntRamMemorySize.name: mgmntRamMemorySize
mgmntRamMemorySize.description: The size of RAM memory measured in number of bytes.

mgmntFlashMemorySize.name: mgmntFlashMemorySize
mgmntFlashMemorySize.description: The size of Flash memory measured in number of bytes.

mgmntNVRamMemorySize.name: mgmntNVRamMemorySize
mgmntNVRamMemorySize.description: The size of Non Volatile Ram memory measured in number of bytes.

mgmnt5vCurrent.name: mgmnt5vCurrent
mgmnt5vCurrent.description: The actual voltage level of this 3.3 volt input as measured in millivolts.

mgmnt5vMin.name: mgmnt5vMin
mgmnt5vMin.description: The minimum operating voltage level of this 5 volt input, measured in millivolts.

mgmnt5vMax.name: mgmnt5vMax
mgmnt5vMax.description: The maximum operating voltage level of this 5 volt input, measured in millivolts.

mgmnt3pt3vCurrent.name: mgmnt3pt3vCurrent
mgmnt3pt3vCurrent.description: The actual voltage level of this 3.3 volt input as measured in millivolts.

mgmnt3pt3vMin.name: mgmnt3pt3vMin
mgmnt3pt3vMin.description: The minimum operating voltage level of this 3.3 volt input, measured in millivolts.

mgmnt3pt3vMax.name: mgmnt3pt3vMax
mgmnt3pt3vMax.description: The maximum operating voltage level of this 3.3 volt input, measured in millivolts.

mgmntDiagnosticBootError.name: mgmntDiagnosticBootError
mgmntDiagnosticBootError.description: This object indicates the status of the diagnostic boot tests. An error is indicated by turning the error indicator on the management module is on.

singleTwisterTable.name: singleTwisterTable
singleTwisterTable.description: A table of information common to single twister modules.

singleTwisterTableEntry.name: singleTwisterTableEntry
singleTwisterTableEntry.description: An entry in the single Twister table of information.

stwEntityIndex.name: stwEntityIndex
stwEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a single twister module for which this entry contains information.

stwLinkLossCarryForward.name: stwLinkLossCarryForward
stwLinkLossCarryForward.description: The ability of an input port to forward the link test pulse to its output port. If disabled the output port will always generate link pulses, regardless of input port link status.

dualTwisterTable.name: dualTwisterTable
dualTwisterTable.description: A table of information common to dual twister modules.

dualTwisterTableEntry.name: dualTwisterTableEntry
dualTwisterTableEntry.description: An entry in the dual Twister table of information.

dtwEntityIndex.name: dtwEntityIndex
dtwEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a dual twister module for which this entry contains information.

dtwLinkLossCarryForward.name: dtwLinkLossCarryForward
dtwLinkLossCarryForward.description: The ability of an input port to forward the link test pulse to its output port. If disabled the output port will always generate link pulses, regardless of input port link status.

redundantTwisterTable.name: redundantTwisterTable
redundantTwisterTable.description: A table of information common to redundant twister modules.

redundantTwisterTableEntry.name: redundantTwisterTableEntry
redundantTwisterTableEntry.description: An entry in the table containing redundant twister information.

rtwEntityIndex.name: rtwEntityIndex
rtwEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a redundant twister module for which this entry contains information.

rtwAutoRestorePrimary.name: rtwAutoRestorePrimary
rtwAutoRestorePrimary.description: This object controls the ability to perform auto restoration back to the primary circuit if a secondary switchover had previously occurred. When rtwModeControl is selectAB then this object is not selectable and a read of this value will always return not selectable.

rtwLinkLossCarryForward.name: rtwLinkLossCarryForward
rtwLinkLossCarryForward.description: The ability of an input port to forward the link test pulse to its output port. If disabled the output port will always generate link pulses, regardless of input port link status.

rtwActivePort.name: rtwActivePort
rtwActivePort.description: This object reflects the port that is both receiving and transmitting packets. If the active port is the secondary then the secondary led indicator will be turned on.

rtwRedundantTransmission.name: rtwRedundantTransmission
rtwRedundantTransmission.description: The ability of the primary and secondary output ports to transmit the received main input signal simultaneously. When rtwModeControl is selectAB then this object is not selectable and a read of this value will always return not-applicable.

rtwSecondarySwitchOver.name: rtwSecondarySwitchOver
rtwSecondarySwitchOver.description: This object reflects whether an automatic switch from the primary port to the secondary port has taken place.

rtwLinkPulseControl.name: rtwLinkPulseControl
rtwLinkPulseControl.description: This object controls the forwarding of the link test pulse to both the primary and secondary ports or the slected port in rtwActivePort. When rtwModeControl is selectAB then this object is not selectable and a read of this value will always return not-applicable.

rtwModeControl.name: rtwModeControl
rtwModeControl.description: This objects selects the operational mode. Redundant mode provides automatic switchover for port failure redundancy while ABSelect provides a basic A/B port selector.

rtwABSelect.name: rtwABSelect
rtwABSelect.description: This object selects the output port that will send and receive packets. If the design of this module does not include the abiltiy to select the mode, then this object will default to not-selectable and no sets to this object will be allowed.

ePortTable.name: ePortTable
ePortTable.description: A table of relevant information about the ports(s) contained within a module.

ePortTableEntry.name: ePortTableEntry
ePortTableEntry.description: An entry in the table containing port related information within a module.

ePortEntityIndex.name: ePortEntityIndex
ePortEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, that identifies a port for which this entry contains information.

ePortIfIndex.name: ePortIfIndex
ePortIfIndex.description: A unique identifier indicating the MIB-II interface number of this port. NOTE: ports on media translators DO NOT conform to MIB-II definition of an interface.

ePortType.name: ePortType
ePortType.description: A unique value that identifies the type of port. Included in the port type is the maximum speed at which this port may operate at and the cable type.

ePortDescription.name: ePortDescription
ePortDescription.description: A textual description of this type of port.

ePortName.name: ePortName
ePortName.description: The user defined name of this port.

ePortLinkStatus.name: ePortLinkStatus
ePortLinkStatus.description: The link status of this port. This status indicates the reception of link test pulse signals generated from an attached device. This object is used in the ePortLinkStatusChangeTrap.

ePortAdminState.name: ePortAdminState
ePortAdminState.description: The desired state of this port. If the design of this module does not include the abiltiy to control this port then this object will default to not-applicable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit control then enable and disable are the only valid states that a user can set this object to. This object is used in the PortControlTrap.

ePortOperStatus.name: ePortOperStatus
ePortOperStatus.description: This object indicates the current operational state of this port.

ePortDuplexAdmin.name: ePortDuplexAdmin
ePortDuplexAdmin.description: This object specifies the desired state of half or full duplex mode for this port. If the design of this module does not include the ability to select duplex, then this object will default to not-applicable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit duplex selection then half and full are the valid states that a user can set this object to.

ePortDuplexOper.name: ePortDuplexOper
ePortDuplexOper.description: This object indicates the current duplex mode of this port.

ePortSpeedAdmin.name: ePortSpeedAdmin
ePortSpeedAdmin.description: This object indicates the current speed that this port is operating at. If the design of this module does not include the abiltiy to control the speed of this then this object will default to not-applicable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit control then all but not-applicable are valid states that a user can set this object to.

ePortSpeedOper.name: ePortSpeedOper
ePortSpeedOper.description: This object specifies the desired speed that this port is operating at.

ePortAutoNegotiationAdmin.name: ePortAutoNegotiationAdmin
ePortAutoNegotiationAdmin.description: This object indicates the current state of auto negotiation for this port. If the design of this module does not include the ability to select auto negotiation, then this object will default to not-applicable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit auto negotiation selection then all but not-applicable are valid states that a user can set this object to.

ePortAutoNegotiationOper.name: ePortAutoNegotiationOper
ePortAutoNegotiationOper.description: This object specifices the desired state of auto negotiation selection. If enabled, this port is capable of auto negotiating full/half duplex and port speed selection.

ePortReset.name: ePortReset
ePortReset.description: The trigger to reset this port. If the design of this module does not include this feature then this object will default to not-resetable and no sets to this object will be allowed. If the design does permit a reset then the only valid state that a user can set this object to is is reset. A read of this object will return either resetable or not-resetable.

ePortActivity.name: ePortActivity
ePortActivity.description: This object indicates data reception and transmision activity on the active port(s).

ePortConnector.name: ePortConnector
ePortConnector.description: This object indicates the connector type that this port supports.

ePortParentRelPos.name: ePortParentRelPos
ePortParentRelPos.description: This object indicates this ports relative position in the module to which it is member of.

serialPortTable.name: serialPortTable
serialPortTable.description: A table of relevent information pertaining to each serial port contained within this system.

serialPortTableEntry.name: serialPortTableEntry
serialPortTableEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing relevant information about a specific serial port contained within this system.

serialPortEntityIndex.name: serialPortEntityIndex
serialPortEntityIndex.description: A unique value, the entPhysicalIndex from the entity MIB, which identifies this serial port.

serialPortDescription.name: serialPortDescription
serialPortDescription.description: A textual description of this type of port.

serialPortName.name: serialPortName
serialPortName.description: The user defined name of this port.

serialPortSpeed.name: serialPortSpeed
serialPortSpeed.description: The speed that this port transmits and receives at.

serialPortDataBits.name: serialPortDataBits
serialPortDataBits.description: The number of bits in a character.

serialPortParity.name: serialPortParity
serialPortParity.description: The port's sense of a character parity bit.

serialPortStopBits.name: serialPortStopBits
serialPortStopBits.description: The number of stop bits for this port.

serialPortFlowControl.name: serialPortFlowControl
serialPortFlowControl.description: The type of flow control for this port.

serialPortConnector.name: serialPortConnector
serialPortConnector.description: This object indicates the connector type that this port supports.

tempStatusChange.name: tempStatusChange
tempStatusChange.description: This trap will be sent when the temperature falls outside of the exceptable range. The values of chassisEntityIndex, chassisCurrentTemp and chassisMaxTemp will be included in this traps varBind list.

backPlaneFailure.name: backPlaneFailure
backPlaneFailure.description: This trap will be sent when there is a backplane failure. The value of modFirstSlot will be included in this traps varBind list.

powerSupply5vChange.name: powerSupply5vChange
powerSupply5vChange.description: This trap will be sent when the voltage from the 5 volt power supply falls outside of the exceptable range. The values of powerSupplyEntityIndex, powerSupply5vCurrent, powerSupplyMin, powerSupply5vMax and powerSupplyUnitIdentifier will be included in this traps varBind list.

powerSupplyStatusChange.name: powerSupplyStatusChange
powerSupplyStatusChange.description: This trap will be sent when a power supply is either turned on or off. The values of powerSupplyEntityIndex, powerSupplyStatus and powerSupplyUnitIdentifier will be included in this traps varBind list.

powerSupplyInsertion.name: powerSupplyInsertion
powerSupplyInsertion.description: This trap will be sent when a power supply is inserted. The values of powerSupplyEntityIndex, powerSupplyType and powerSupplyUnitIdentifier will be included in this traps varBind list.

powerSupplyRemoval.name: powerSupplyRemoval
powerSupplyRemoval.description: This trap will be sent when a power supply is removed. The values of powerSupplyEntityIndex, powerSupplyType and powerSupplyUnitIdentifier will be included in this traps varBind list.

chassisEntityReset.name: chassisEntityReset
chassisEntityReset.description: This trap is sent when a chassis is reset. The values of lastEntityResetIndex, lastEntityResetReason, and lastEntityResetTime will be included in this traps varBind list.

moduleEntityReset.name: moduleEntityReset
moduleEntityReset.description: This trap is sent when a module is reset. The values of lastEntityResetIndex, lastEntityResetReason, and lastEntityResetTime, modType, modFirstSlot and modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.

eportEntityReset.name: eportEntityReset
eportEntityReset.description: This trap is sent when a port is reset. The values of lastEntityResetIndex, lastEntityResetReason, and lastEntityResetTime, modType, modFirstSlot, modNumSlotsOccupied, and ePortParentRelPos will be included in this traps varBind list.

moduleInsertion.name: moduleInsertion
moduleInsertion.description: This trap is sent when a module is inserted to a slot. The values of modEntityIndex, modFirstSlot, modType, modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.

moduleRemoval.name: moduleRemoval
moduleRemoval.description: This trap is sent when a module is removed from a slot. The values of modEntityIndex, modFirstSlot, modType, modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.

unknownModule.name: unknownModule
unknownModule.description: This trap is sent when a module is inserted and it's type cannot be determined. The values of modEntityIndex, modType, modFirstSlot, modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.

moduleFailure.name: moduleFailure
moduleFailure.description: This trap is sent when a module fails and thus is inaccessible. The value of modFirtSlot will be included in this traps varBind list.

ePortLinkStatusChange.name: ePortLinkStatusChange
ePortLinkStatusChange.description: This trap is sent when there is a change in the link state of a port. The values of ePortLinkStatus, ePortIndex, modType, modFirstSlot, and modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.

ePortAdminChange.name: ePortAdminChange
ePortAdminChange.description: This trap is sent when a user changes the admin state of a port from enable to disable or vice versa. The values of ePortAdminState ePortEntityIndex, modType, modFirstSlot, modNumSlotsOccupied, will be included in this traps varBind list.

rtwSwitchOverChange.name: rtwSwitchOverChange
rtwSwitchOverChange.description: This trap is sent when a switchover from the primary to the secondary port and vice versa has occured. The values of rtwEntityIndex, rtwActivePort, modFirstSlot, modNumSlotsOccupied will be included in this traps varBind list.
